# Trivy ignore rules for overwatch-gitops K8s manifests
# These findings are acknowledged but cannot be safely remediated
# Format: one rule ID per line (comments above for context)

# Seedbox (sonarr/radarr/prowlarr): LinuxServer.io s6-overlay requires
# SETGID, SETUID, CHOWN, FOWNER, DAC_OVERRIDE capabilities for init.
# Runs as root during init, drops to PUID/PGID 1000 for app processes.
# DO NOT apply "drop: ALL" or "allowPrivilegeEscalation: false" — this
# breaks s6-overlay init and causes a crash loop. Custom SCC
# "linuxserver-io" grants minimum required capabilities.
# Risk accepted: least-privilege caps, app runs as UID 1000 after init.
KSV012
KSV014
KSV106

# Newt tunnel: requires root + privilege escalation for WireGuard
# tun device, network namespace ops, UDP binding. Writable rootfs
# needed for /tmp/healthy health check.
# Risk accepted: single-purpose container, network policy restricted.
KSV012
KSV014
KSV106
